  "text": "In Aprameya et al. there was an increase in mean weight from 9.2kg (2.0 SD) at discharge to 10.3kg (2.2) at 12-months for children without underlying illness (p<0.001) [CITATION_1] . The same increase was observed for children with underlying illnesses from 8.1kg (2.4) to 8.9kg (2.6) (p<0.001), albeit lower at each time point. The difference in weight gain between groups was also significant (p<0.001).",
